        "title": "Europe's pension time bomb",
        "title_zh": "欧洲的养老金定时炸弹",
        "url": "https://www.economist.com/leaders/2026/07/04/europes-pension-time-bomb",
        "summary_md": "### 一句话核心主旨\n**欧洲主要国家养老金体系的隐性负债已超过显性政府债务总和,代际不公正在制度化。**\n\n### 核心观点与论据拆解\n- **观点 1**: 法国、意大利、西班牙养老金支付占 GDP 比重将在 2040 年突破 17%\n  - **论据**: 欧盟委员会《2025 老龄化报告》预测上述三国养老金支出增速将远超 GDP 增速\n- **观点 2**: 法定退休年龄每推迟一年,可减少负债相当于 GDP 的 3%\n  - **论据**: OECD 跨国比较显示,延迟退休是单一最有效的福利可持续工具\n\n### 高频词汇提炼\n| 英文术语 | 中文译法 | 语境释义 |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| unfunded liabilities | 隐性负债 | 已承诺但无对应资产的未来支付义务 |\n| dependency ratio | 抚养比 | 退休人口与劳动年龄人口之比 |\n| parametric reform | 参数性改革 | 通过调整缴费率、退休年龄等参数实现体系平衡 |\n",
        "content_raw": "<h1>Europe's pension time bomb</h1><p>The promises politicians made to their parents are coming due.</p><p>Across the European Union, public pension promises have grown far faster than the tax bases needed to fund them. The European Commission's 2025 ageing report estimates that pension spending will rise to 13.9% of EU GDP by 2040, up from 11.3% today.</p><p>In Italy, France and Spain, the figure will exceed 17%. That is larger than each country's defence budget, education spending and infrastructure investment combined.</p><h2>The reform no one dares</h2><p>Raising the statutory retirement age by one year reduces lifetime pension liabilities by roughly 3% of GDP, according to the OECD. No other single policy lever comes close.</p>"
